SKILL_NAME: Identify and use text features (e.g., captions, bold print, subheadings, glossaries, indexes, electronic menus, icons) to locate information efficiently
Analyze in detail how the causal relationships between individuals, events, and ideas are introduced and developed in an informational text
Accurately read unfamiliar grade-appropriate multisyllabic words in isolation, using knowledge of word morphology (e.g., autograph, construction)
Read regularly and independently in fifth-grade-appropriate texts for sustained periods of time, increasing speed, stamina, and comprehension
Recognize one's first name in print
Recognize that words with similar meanings (e.g., house and home) evoke different responses
Analyze in detail how the similarities and differences between key individuals, events, or ideas are introduced and developed in an informational text
Recognize an author's use of propaganda or slanted text, analyzing how the language or ideas advance the author's purpose
Use knowledge of frequently occurring affixes (e.g., un-, re-), base words, and their inflectional forms (e.g., look + -ing) as clues to the meanings of words (e.g., unhappy, looking)
